This paper deals with a geometric network design problem, which involves selecting points in compact neighborhoods in $\mathbb{R}^d$ to maximize the length of the longest spanning tree. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG), as it involves geometric objects and their properties. It also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for finding an approximation algorithm with a certain ratio. The problem can be formulated as an optimization problem, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithmic approach involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.GT).
